  ],
  "text": "Found all five requested files in the sg-evals/firefox--871325b8 repository under security/nss/lib/ssl/:\n\n1. ssl3con.c — Implements SSL 3.0/TLS record processing and cipher suite negotiation. This is the core TLS protocol handler covering handshake, cipher suite selection, record encryption/decryption, and MAC operations for SSL 3.0 through TLS 1.2.\n\n2. tls13con.c — Implements TLS 1.3 handshake and record processing. Handles the TLS 1.3 handshake state machine, key schedule (via HKDF), early data (0-RTT), and record layer processing specific to TLS 1.3.\n\n3. dtlscon.c — Implements DTLS-specific protocol handling. Covers DTLS record layer, retransmission logic, epoch management, and the adaptations needed for datagram transport (UDP) compared to stream-based TLS.\n\n4. ssl3ecc.c — Implements ECC (Elliptic Curve Cryptography) cipher suite operations. Handles ECDH key exchange, ECDSA signatures, EC group negotiation, and related elliptic curve operations for SSL/TLS.\n\n5. sslexp.h — Header file declaring experimental SSL APIs. Exposes non-standard, experimental extensions and APIs that are not yet part of the public stable SSL API surface."
}

